From: Olly Betts <olly@survex.com>
Date: Tue, 28 Nov 2017 17:50:38 +1300
Subject: [PATCH] Avoid char * array members in the library

This reduces relocations at dynamic library load time, which reduces
the time to load the library.
---
 xapian-core/backends/glass/glass_compact.cc | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/xapian-core/backends/glass/glass_compact.cc b/xapian-core/backends/glass/glass_compact.cc
index ab22380bb74..8e904dd16bc 100644
--- a/xapian-core/backends/glass/glass_compact.cc
+++ b/xapian-core/backends/glass/glass_compact.cc
@@ -784,7 +784,7 @@ GlassDatabase::compact(Xapian::Compactor * compactor,
 {
     struct table_list {
 	// The "base name" of the table.
-	const char * name;
+	char name[9];
 	// The type.
 	Glass::table_type type;
 	// Create tables after position lazily.
